# Dual feeds (strategy ↔ product)

**Contract SoT:** [`docs/protocol/dual-feed.md`](../../docs/protocol/dual-feed.md)

## Outbound (this silo)

- Canonical handoff for www builders: `docs/www-feed.md`
- When strategy changes affect the product (direction, pricing, supply, UX intent, open questions) → update `docs/www-feed.md` **same turn** (Meta date + Changelog line)
- When Brian states product ideas in a **business** chat → add/update **Product proposals** (and lane proposals if useful) on `www-feed.md` **same turn** — do not wait for Brian to re-type them in www
- Graduate backlog stubs → Ready for planning only when Brian says so explicitly **or** when he clearly authorizes agents to pass items as Ready/proposals
- **Never** edit `codex-www/` (pins, lanes, plans, product code) from this silo
- Lane names in the feed are **proposals** until www adopts them in `lanes.md`

## Inbound (www → business)

- Www-owned: `/mnt/DataStore/Ventures/project-codex/codex-www/docs/business-feed.md` (schema in contract)
- On resume / before foundation–GTM–monetization work → **read** business-feed (if present)
- When new signals appear → update affected `docs/` and **refresh dashboard pins** same turn (`strategy-queue.md` + sector files; `build-order.md` if plans change); update `product-signals.md` harvest
- Do not write the www vault; if feed is missing, keep a Ready row on www-feed asking www to create it

## Pin refresh (Brian does not maintain feeds)

After any meaningful feed or strategy edit this turn → refresh affected `.cursor/dashboard/` sector file(s) + `strategy-queue.md` (and `build-order.md` when plans change). Prefer `open_resource` on pins touched.
